            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped leek</strong> to the dish with the <strong>shallot quarters</strong>, <strong>carrot batons </strong>and<strong> halved potatoes</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>,<strong> fennel seeds</strong>, 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[510ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tear your<strong> 'Nduja </strong>into the dish (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663092326631-x200.jpg",
