            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663092331763-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has had 50 min, remove the dish<strong> </strong>from the oven and stir in your <strong>crème fraiche</strong>, keeping the pork belly skin-side up, then return the dish to the oven for 7-8 min or until thick and saucy – this is your <strong>baked</strong> <strong>spicy pork belly & 'Nduja stew</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until beginning to crisp</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
